<subsection xml:id="frq1b2-countOccurrences">
<title>String Algorithm - Count Occurrences</title>

<activity label="frq1b2-countOccurrences">
<statement>
<p>Write a method called countOccurrences that determines how many times a specific target string appears within a larger text string.</p>
<p>Be careful! It is easy to end up with an infinite loop if you are not careful when updating your loop variable. You will need to use the indexOf method to find the next occurrence of the target string, and then update your loop variable to start searching for the next occurrence after the current one.</p>
</statement>

<program interactive="activecode" language="java">
<code>
public class PhraseAnalyzer {
    public static int countOccurrences(String text, String target) {
        
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Test 1: Multiple occurrences
        String text1 = "cat bat rat cat";
        String target1 = "cat";
        System.out.println("Text: " + text1 + " | Target: " + target1);
        System.out.println("Count: " + PhraseAnalyzer.countOccurrences(text1, target1)); // Expected: 2
        System.out.println();

        // Test 2: Target not in text
        String text2 = "The quick brown fox";
        String target2 = "dog";
        System.out.println("Text: " + text2 + " | Target: " + target2);
        System.out.println("Count: " + PhraseAnalyzer.countOccurrences(text2, target2)); // Expected: 0
        System.out.println();

        // Test 3: Entire text is the target
        String text3 = "Java";
        String target3 = "Java";
        System.out.println("Text: " + text3 + " | Target: " + target3);
        System.out.println("Count: " + PhraseAnalyzer.countOccurrences(text3, target3)); // Expected: 1
    }
}
</code>
<tests>
